# Custom i18n System - Evidive Rules

> Based on project implementation in lib/i18n/
> Supports 11 languages: fr, en, de, es, it, pt, nl, pl, el, ru, sv

## ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS (ZERO TOLERANCE)

### Universal
- NO placeholders: `TODO`, `FIXME`, `XXX`, `HACK`
- NO hardcoded user-facing strings
- NO missing translations in any of the 11 languages

### i18n Specific
- NO using URL-based locale prefixes (project uses cookie-based)
- NO hardcoded locale strings - use `Locale` type
- NO skipping translation for new features
- NO incomplete message files

## SUPPORTED LOCALES

```typescript
export const locales = ['fr', 'en', 'de', 'es', 'it', 'pt', 'nl', 'pl', 'el', 'ru', 'sv'] as const

export type Locale = (typeof locales)[number]

export const defaultLocale: Locale = 'fr'
```

## REQUIRED Patterns

### Server Component Translation

```typescript
// In Server Components
import { getTranslations } from '@/lib/i18n/get-translations-server'

export default async function Page() {
  const t = await getTranslations('home')
  
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{t.hero.title}</h1>
      <p>{t.hero.subtitle}</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Client Component Translation

```typescript
'use client'

import { useTranslations } from '@/lib/i18n/use-translations'

export function ClientComponent() {
  const { t, locale } = useTranslations('common')
  
  return (
    <button>
      {t.buttons.submit}
    </button>
  )
}
```

