### Adding New Translations

When adding new features, you MUST:

1. Add keys to ALL 11 message files:
```bash
# Check completeness with script
npm run check:i18n
```

2. Structure translations by feature:
```json
{
  "booking": {
    "form": {
      "title": "Réserver une plongée",
      "date": "Date de la plongée",
      "participants": "Nombre de participants"
    },
    "confirmation": {
      "title": "Réservation confirmée",
      "reference": "Référence"
    }
  }
}
```

### Multilingual Database Content

For user-generated content (center names, descriptions), use JSON columns:

```typescript
// Prisma schema
model Center {
  name        Json // { fr: "...", en: "...", es: "..." }
  description Json
}

// Usage
function getLocalizedName(center: Center, locale: Locale): string {
  const names = center.name as Record<string, string>
  return names[locale] || names['en'] || names['fr'] || ''
}
```

### Locale Detection Flow

1. Check `NEXT_LOCALE` cookie
2. Parse `Accept-Language` header
3. Default to `fr`

```typescript
// middleware.ts already handles this
// DO NOT add locale prefixes to URLs
```

### OpenGraph Locale Mapping

```typescript
import { getOpenGraphLocale } from '@/lib/i18n/config'

export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  const locale = await getLocale()
  
  return {
    openGraph: {
      locale: getOpenGraphLocale(locale), // e.g., 'fr_FR'
    }
  }
}
```

## FORBIDDEN Patterns

### Wrong: Hardcoded strings
```tsx
// WRONG
<button>Submit</button>

// CORRECT
<button>{t.buttons.submit}</button>
```

### Wrong: URL-based locale
```tsx
// WRONG - Project doesn't use URL prefixes
<Link href="/fr/about">About</Link>

// CORRECT - Clean URLs
<Link href="/about">About</Link>
// Locale is in cookie, not URL
```

### Wrong: Incomplete translations
```json
// WRONG - Missing in other languages
// Only in messages/fr.json, not in en.json, de.json, etc.
{
  "newFeature": {
    "title": "Nouvelle fonctionnalité"
  }
}

// CORRECT - Add to ALL 11 files
```

### Wrong: Inline locale switch
```tsx
// WRONG - Hardcoded locale
const name = center.name['fr']

// CORRECT - Use current locale
const name = getLocalizedName(center, locale)
```

## Language Switcher

```tsx
'use client'

import { useLocale, setLocale } from '@/lib/i18n'
import { locales, localeNames, localeFlags } from '@/lib/i18n/config'

export function LanguageSwitcher() {
  const currentLocale = useLocale()
  
  return (
    <select 
      value={currentLocale}
      onChange={(e) => setLocale(e.target.value as Locale)}
    >
      {locales.map(locale => (
        <option key={locale} value={locale}>
          {localeFlags[locale]} {localeNames[locale]}
        </option>
      ))}
    </select>
  )
}
```

## Verification Script

Run before commits to ensure all translations are complete:

```bash
npm run check:i18n
```

This will flag:
- Missing keys in any language file
- Keys present in some files but not others
- Empty translation values

## Enforcement

This rule file has `alwaysApply: true`. Violations will be:
1. Flagged immediately
2. Blocked from generation
3. Required to be fixed before proceeding
